<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 11:10PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Pushmataha, southwestern Latimer and southern Pittsburg Counties
through MIDNIGHT CDT...
At 1110 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
northwest of Daisy, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Krebs...
Kiowa...                          Savanna...
Alderson...                       Mcalester Regional Airport...
Blanco...                         Haileyville...
Pittsburg...                      Sardis...
Bache...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
